Going from the point on the left to the point on the right, the change in $y$ is $\purpleD{-8}$, and the change in $x$ is $\redD 5$.

$\begin{align}
\text{Slope}=\dfrac{\purpleD{\text{rise}}}{\redD{\text{run}}}=\dfrac{\purpleD{\Delta y}}{\redD{\Delta x}}&=\dfrac{\purpleD{-8}}{\redD{5}}
\\\\
&=-\dfrac85
\end{align}$

