$\begin{align}
\text{Slope}&=\dfrac{-3-5}{-3-(-6)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-8}{3}
\\\\
&=-\dfrac{8}{3}
\end{align}$

The equation is $y=-\dfrac{8}{3}x+b$ for some $b$.

Let's find the slope between $(\blueD{-5},\blueD{4})$ and $(\maroonD{1},\maroonD{6})$:

$\begin{align}
\text{Slope}&=\dfrac{\maroonD{6}-\blueD{4}}{\maroonD{1}-\blueD{(-5)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{2}{6}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{3}
\end{align}$

